{"summary":"Five amendments identify real defects or spec-conformance problems in the current implementation. One amendment overstates its case: the ordering dependency around `safe_plan_hash_backfill` is real, but the codebase already has regression tests that would fail if that ordering were broken, so I would not treat that amendment as an outstanding issue.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-19-a8837f43","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified in code: `TaskRunLineagePort`, `record_bead_start`, and `update_task_run` still take `run_id: Option<&str>` and `plan_hash: Option<&str>`. The runless matching paths remain in `find_matching_running_task_run`, `matching_finalized_task_runs`, and the fs update logic, and the snapshot-derived helpers `snapshot_plan_hash`, `safe_plan_hash_backfill`, and `snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation` are still present. `fs.rs` also explicitly documents a deliberate deviation from Issue 3 acceptance criteria. Whatever the engineering rationale, the implementation did not carry out the required-contract change described by the amendment."},{"amendment_id":"fr-19-33dc0ec6","decision":"accept","rationale":"`FsTaskRunLineageStore::snapshot_plan_hash` directly calls `FsMilestoneSnapshotStore.read_snapshot`, so the lineage adapter is hard-wired to the filesystem snapshot adapter instead of depending only on the port boundary. That creates a real substitution hazard: the service layer can be composed with other `MilestoneSnapshotPort` implementations, but this lineage store will still read the filesystem snapshot. That is avoidable cross-adapter coupling and a maintainability/architecture defect."},{"amendment_id":"fr-19-20d95d35","decision":"reject","rationale":"The ordering dependency is real, but the amendment's core claim that a reorder would fail silently \"with no error or test failure\" is not true in the current codebase. There are already regression tests that finalize a running entry with `plan_hash=None` and assert backfill occurs, including `plan_hash_auto_populated_from_snapshot` and `safe_backfill_fills_plan_hash_when_snapshot_unchanged`. Reordering `safe_plan_hash_backfill` after `entry.outcome = outcome` would break those tests. A helper could still make the code clearer, but the amendment overstates the current risk and does not identify an unprotected defect."},{"amendment_id":"fr-19-0b8774c0","decision":"accept","rationale":"`unique_terminal_replay_match` explicitly describes the `(Some(run_id), None)` case as an internal caller bug, yet it returns `AppError::CorruptRecord`. Because `CorruptRecord` renders as a corruption diagnosis, this conflates programmer error with damaged persisted data. The message text softens that, but the variant choice is still semantically wrong and can mislead triage or any future variant-based handling."},{"amendment_id":"fr-19-cd84c211","decision":"accept","rationale":"The code still allows runless lifecycle handling. `run_id` remains optional in the service and lineage-port APIs, `find_matching_running_task_run` and `matching_finalized_task_runs` still contain started-at-based fallback for runless entries, and the fs update path still backfills a runless open row when a named completion arrives. The tests also codify this behavior. If the intended contract was to require run identity at the API boundary and remove runless matching, that change is not implemented."},{"amendment_id":"fr-19-9910b1f5","decision":"accept","rationale":"`plan_hash` is still optional in the service/port APIs, and the snapshot-derived machinery remains active through `snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation`, `snapshot_plan_hash`, and `safe_plan_hash_backfill`. The tests explicitly preserve this behavior by asserting that omitted `plan_hash` values can later be filled from snapshot provenance when conditions allow. If the required contract was to make `plan_hash` mandatory at bead start and remove snapshot-based derivation/backfill, the implementation still diverges from that requirement."}]}